{
  "text": "Seizures and mental retardation are common and represent the clinical manifestations of the neuronal migration disorder with lissencephaly type II. In MEB disease the brainstem is characteristically flattened. Visual impairment is caused by progressive myopia associated with retinal degeneration but does not reach the level of gravity seen in WWS. Optic colobomas, glaucoma, and cataracts are common [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
